<subSubSection id="1BB46528FF94FFDC08ABFF3FF331FE10" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="531136A3FF94FFDC08ABFF3FF331FE10" blockId="5.[151,1436,153,395]" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">
Comment: 
<bibRefCitation id="373F4B52FF94FFDC092AFF3FF3A3FF4C" author="Moure, J. S." box="[326,484,188,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" pagination="939 - 951" refId="ref4995" refString="Moure, J. S. (1995) Reestudo de alguns tipos de abelhas neotropicais descritos por Friese e conservados no Museu de Berlim (Apoidea, Colletidae, Anthophoridae). Revista Brasileira de Zoologia, 12, 939 - 951. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0101 - 81751995000400021" type="journal article" year="1995">Moure (1995)</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<taxonomicName id="94AE4D20FF94FFDC0A31FF3FF10DFF4C" authorityName="Fox. This" authorityYear="1899" box="[605,842,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xylocopoides">
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0A31FF3FF10DFF4C" box="[605,842,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">Centris xylocopoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="94AE4D20FF94FFDC0C23FF3FF7C4FF4C" authority="Packard, 1869" authorityName="Packard" authorityYear="1869" box="[1103,1411,189,215]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="braccata">
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0C23FF3FF625FF4C" box="[1103,1122,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0C1DFF3FF692FF4C" box="[1137,1237,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">braccata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="373F4B52FF94FFDC0CB2FF3FF7C4FF4C" author="Packard, A. S." box="[1246,1411,189,215]" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" pagination="52 - 69" refId="ref5135" refString="Packard, A. S. (1869) List of Hymenopterous and Lepidopterous insects collected by the Smithsonian expedition to South America, under Prof. James Orton. Annual Report of the Trustees of the Peabody Academy of Sciences, 1, 52 - 69." type="journal article" year="1869">Packard, 1869</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a very large and robust bee described from 
<collectingCountry id="2BB97633FF94FFDC0A1FFF63F0EDFF60" box="[627,682,225,251]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">Peru</collectingCountry>
. The study of the 
<typeStatus id="8C158801FF94FFDC0B16FF63F1EDFF60" box="[890,938,225,251]" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">type</typeStatus>
specimens of both species showed they are superficially similar in the patterns of coloration of the integument and pubescence. Despite this apparent similarity, both are actually different species, so the synonymy proposed by him and subsequently accepted by 
<bibRefCitation id="373F4B52FF94FFDC0D7CFEABF2A3FEFC" author="Moure, J. S. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F." pageId="5" pageNumber="483" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref5052" refString="Moure, J. S., Melo, G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo, F. (2007) Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell, 1901. In: Moure, J. S., Urban, D. &amp; Melo, G. A. R. (Eds.), Catalogue of bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitiba, pp. 83 - 142." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0D0FFEA8F7D2FED8" box="[1379,1429,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">et al</emphasis>
. (2007)
</bibRefCitation>
, is incorrect. The name 
<taxonomicName id="94AE4D20FF94FFDC0995FECFF0E9FEFC" authorityName="Fox. This" authorityYear="1899" box="[505,686,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xylocopoides">
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0995FECFF04BFEFC" box="[505,524,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0A70FECFF0E9FEFC" box="[540,686,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">xylocopoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here withdrawn from the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="94AE4D20FF94FFDC0CFFFECFF75DFEFC" authorityName="Packard" authorityYear="1869" box="[1171,1306,333,359]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="braccata">
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0CFFFECFF6E1FEFC" box="[1171,1190,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="61DAEAB1FF94FFDC0CDAFECFF75DFEFC" box="[1206,1306,333,359]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="483">braccata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and consequently revalidated.
</paragraph>
